ould be more organized- Not necessarily a con, but there is a lot of work to do. There are occasions when I wish we had more time or people- On the flip side, sometimes I wish we had less people during lunch because the table fills up quick lolAdvice to ManagementI've never had a better job and I'd bet most of my coworkers feel the same way. So please just keep doing the things you've been doing! Cratejoy 2017-01-31 11:17 PST Dec 6, 2016"What's Not To Like?"StarStarStarStarStarWork/Life BalanceCulture & ValuesCareer OpportunitiesComp & BenefitsSenior ManagementCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Austin, TXCurrent Employee - Anonymous Employee in Austin, TXRecommendsPositive OutlookI have been working at Cratejoy full-time (More than a year)ProsIncredible, supportive team that all works hard together; ability to self-manage, which is an offset of having a group of super competent people; awesome downtown office with casual in-office vibes; fun team events + perks galore; the feeling of being a part of something really awesome; loads of transparency; office dogs.ConsYou will work hard and long which is not necessarily a con, but I don't think anyone finds their job at Cratejoy "easy." People come in ready to crush it and perform at high levels and some people aren't for that.Advice to ManagementKeep making good hires and cultivating a positive and open environment. Avoid letting departments get too cliquey. Cratejoy 2016-12-06 07:53 PST See All 15 ReviewsGet email updates for jobs like this:Job Title or KeywordsLocationEnter Email AddressCreate AlertCreatingOne more step! Please check your email to activate the job alert.Cratejoy PhotosSee All PhotosSee AllView Allnum of numClose (Esc)Interested in a New Job?Upload a resume to mobile apply.
